Description: Sherd of neck and shoulder of very worn East Greek pottery oenochoe; slight ridge at base of lip; highly micaceous buff-brown clay; ancient repair hole and indentation; inscription on neck.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Well 100 (= Well 2) (said to be)
Curator's comments: A. Johnston, 'Some fictile biographies from Naukratis', in D.C. Kurtz (ed.), Essays in Classical Archaeology for Eleni Hatzivassiliou, Oxford 2008, 116 and 120 fig. 2. Almost certainly from the same jug as 1965,0930.509, which is equally worn but with probable traces of glaze.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.030)
